;; kotoba-lang/compiler's capability-name registry (ADR-2607182410).
;;
;; Maps a namespaced-keyword capability NAME (as written in `.kotoba` source,
;; e.g. `(cap-call :identity/sign msg)`) to the small integer capability id
;; `cap-call`'s existing [0,255] wire format already uses. This lets a
;; `.kotoba` program name a capability instead of writing a magic number,
;; while the compiler still lowers to the EXACT SAME `[:cap-call <int>]`
;; KIR node / `[:cap/call <id>]` effect the integer form has always produced
;; -- name resolution happens once, at parse/desugar time, strictly inside
;; `kotoba.compiler.frontend`, before HIR/KIR construction. Nothing
;; downstream (`admission.cljc`, `verifier.clj`, any backend) is aware a
;; keyword was ever written.
;;
;; This id space is COMPILER-LOCAL and intentionally NOT shared with any
;; other repo's capability table -- in particular, it is deliberately NOT
;; the same registry as `kotoba-core-contracts`'
;; `resources/kotoba/runtime/capability_contract.edn` (that file names a
;; different host ABI, owned by a different codebase, with its own id
;; space starting at 201; reusing/aliasing it here was considered and
;; explicitly rejected by the design ADR -- this compiler's own [0,255]
;; `cap-call` ids and that runtime's ids are independent numbering systems
;; that happen to share some human-readable names). Do not attempt to keep
;; the two files' ids in sync; only the NAMES are allowed to coincide, and
;; only because both happen to describe similar real-world capabilities.
;;
;; Ids are unique small integers in [1, 255] (0 is left unassigned so a
;; missing/zeroed id can never silently resolve to a real capability).
;; Adding a new capability name: append an entry with the next unused id;
;; never renumber or reuse a retired id (a retired name should be deleted
;; outright, not reassigned, since existing compiled artifacts may still
;; reference its numeric id directly via the pre-existing literal-int form).
{:identity/sign 1
 :identity/verify 2
 :hash/sha256 3
 :http/post 4
 :log/read 5
 :log/append 6
 :clock/now 7}
